&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DCP: Director, Ticketing Sales &amp;amp; Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dick Clark Productions (DCP), the&amp;nbsp;world&#39;s largest producer and proprietor of televised live event entertainment programming, is hiring a Director of Ticketing Sales &amp;amp; Operations to be responsible for leading ticketing sales strategy and execution across Dick Clark Productions&#39; portfolio of live events. This role will drive ticket sales performance through pricing optimization, inventory management, sales analytics, and cross-functional collaboration while ensuring seamless execution throughout the ticketing lifecycle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate brings a strong understanding of live event ticketing, proven experience managing complex ticketing operations, and the ability to leverage data and market insights to identify growth opportunities and improve performance across a diverse portfolio of events.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As DCP values in-person collaboration and team cohesion, employees work onsite 4 days a week and 1 day remotely with a focus on maintaining a vibrant and inclusive culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Strategy &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As the primary ticketing stakeholder at DCP, partner with the executive leadership team to develop, implement, and optimize ticketing strategies across all ticketed events, driving revenue growth, audience acquisition, and operational excellence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the end-to-end ticketing lifecycle, including event builds, inventory management, pricing strategy, on-sale execution, reporting, financial reconciliation, and post-event settlement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with ticketing platforms, venue box offices, promoters, and third-party vendors to manage event inventory, seat holds, ticket releases, access control, and dynamic pricing initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design data-driven campaigns, pricing models, and outreach plans to maximize live event ticket revenue and audience attendance by analyzing market trends, setting pricing models, and developing promotional campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor ticket sales performance, market trends, and consumer demand patterns, providing actionable insights and strategic recommendations to senior leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and implement process improvements, technology solutions, and operational efficiencies to enhance sales performance, reporting capabilities, and overall event profitability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with finance teams to support event settlements by preparing ticketing reports, validating sales and fee reconciliations, interpreting ticketing audits, and ensuring financial accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee complex seating strategy and inventory allocation across all events, balancing public onsales with VIP, sponsor, artist, executive, media, production, and partner requirements while maximizing revenue opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage all ticket holds and specialty inventory, including RTP, complimentary, house seats, sponsor allocations, artist and talent requests, ensuring accurate tracking, timely releases, and adherence to approved allocation strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct seating manifest development and optimization, coordinating cross-functional stakeholder requests and executing seat relocations, upgrades, and last-minute accommodations while preserving premium inventory and guest experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead day-of-show ticketing operations in partnership with venue box offices, talent teams, credentialing teams, and event operations, resolving ticketing issues, managing will call and VIP fulfillment, and ensuring seamless guest entry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain comprehensive ticketing re

&lt;p&gt;Fairchild Media Group is seeking an experienced and creative &lt;strong&gt;Associate Editor, Strategic Content Development&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to oversee custom content production at Fairchild&amp;nbsp;Studio, the custom content studio for WWD, Beauty Inc and Footwear News. The ideal candidate will have a deep understanding of B2B content creation, editorial storytelling, and the digital media landscape. The role is ideal for a journalist with a strong sense of news who can also spot trends and produce well-written stories in a compelling way.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage development and execution of custom content programs including native articles and stories, research reports, multimedia content hubs, video, podcasts and social, as well as moderation of live panels and webinars.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Editorial news reporting and special features across all FMG publications) focused on fashion apparel, retail, beauty, luxury goods, accessories, textiles, and retail real estate as well as the technologies that support these segments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the sales and marketing teams to ideate content proposals and to meet with clients and assess their content needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sourcing interviews, conducting market research, and identifying industry trends, such as changes in consumer behavior, emerging technologies such as generative AI, and the impact of macroeconomic forces on business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimization of content for SEO, social, syndication, and other referral sources, and ability to leverage traffic analytics to increase engagement and grow audience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 5-7 years of professional writing/editing experience, specifically with B2B focus within the fashion apparel, retail, beauty, and related segments&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong editorial judgment and ability to distill market trends, assess the content needs of sponsors and work under strict deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational skills, the ability to manage several projects at once and work under tight deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Well-versed in digital strategy, analytics, and SEO best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for fashion apparel, retail, beauty, and technology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As PMC values in-person collaboration and team cohesion, employees work onsite 4 days a week and 1 day remotely, with a focus on maintaining a vibrant and inclusive culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A good faith estimate of the salary range is $70k - $80,000 upon hire. Factors that could be used to determine your actual salary may include your specific skills, years of experience and comparison to current employees already in this role. If you have more or less experience than specified on this job posting, please apply and list your salary expectations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If hired, employee will be in an “at-will position” and the Company reserves the right to modify base salary (as well as any other discretionary payment or compensation program) at any time, including for reasons related to individual performance, Company or individual department/team performance, and market factors).&lt;/p&gt;
