&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fairchild: Events Producer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fairchild Live&lt;/strong&gt;, the events arm of Fairchild Media Group under &lt;strong&gt;Penske Media Corporation (PMC)&lt;/strong&gt;, is adding an Events Producer to its high-energy, fast-growing team. Fairchild is home to iconic brands including&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Women’s Wear Daily (WWD)&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Footwear News (FN), and Beauty Inc., &lt;/strong&gt;and sits at the center of the global fashion, beauty, and retail industries. WWD, often called the “fashion bible,” is where &lt;strong&gt;decision-makers go to understand where the industry is headed and why it matters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you’ll help bring to life high-profile regional and international events attended by industry leaders, creatives, and executives. As the day-to-day project lead, the Events Producer will lead and execute events from start to finish while collaborating closely with editorial, sales, and marketing teams to deliver standout experiences that meet brand and business goals. This is an ideal opportunity for someone passionate about fashion and beauty, energized by live events, and excited by global travel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As PMC values in-person collaboration and team cohesion, employees work onsite 4 days a week and 1 day remotely with a focus on maintaining a vibrant and inclusive culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Event Execution &amp;amp; Project Management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the day-to-day event lead on assigned programs, managing the full event lifecycle from initial planning through on-site execution and post-event wrap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and manage detailed event timelines, run-of-show documents, and production schedules to ensure seamless execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate deliverables across creative, editorial, marketing, sales, and events teams to keep all stakeholders aligned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead on-site operations including load-in, live event execution, and breakdown.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage speaker and talent logistics in partnership with editorial and programming teams, including green room management, on-site coordination, and travel planning when applicable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Venue &amp;amp; Vendor Coordination&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research, recommend, and secure venues/platforms that fit budget and audience needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own day-to-day vendor and venue communication, including sourcing, contract support, negotiations, and ongoing relationship management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee venue and platform selection end-to-end, from research and recommendations through budget alignment and contract execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Creative &amp;amp; Branding Support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the execution and interpretation of established brand guidelines across signage and event look and feel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development of look-and-feel decks and activation presentations, translating approved branding into compelling, execution-ready event concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the full event design expression, including florals, staging, and sponsor activations, ensuring cohesive on-brand delivery across all environments and touchpoints.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Financial &amp;amp; Tracking&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own event financial tracking, including vendor quotes, expenses, and invoicing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead event reconciliations and budget reporting, ensuring accuracy and clear visibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post-Event&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with event recaps, reporting, and team debriefs to capture learnings and improve future activations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure events deliver against defined business, brand, and audience go

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fairchild Media Group: Social Media Editor&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fairchild Media Group is looking for a sharp, creative Social Media Editor to help power the daily social presence of our iconic brands—WWD, Footwear News, Beauty Inc, and Sourcing Journal — with a primary focus on WWD.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role sits at the intersection of journalism, visual storytelling, and real-time culture. You’ll play a key role in translating breaking news, original reporting, and standout visuals into engaging, platform-native content that resonates across social. Working closely with the Social Media Director, you’ll help drive daily publishing, shape and package content, and ensure timely, engaging content that reflect each brand’s distinct voice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a fast-paced, highly collaborative role ideal for someone with strong editorial instincts, excellent writing skills, and a deep understanding of how social platforms actually work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FMG values in-person collaboration and team cohesion, employees work onsite 4 days a week and 1 day remotely with a focus on maintaining a vibrant and inclusive culture.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support daily social publishing across Instagram, TikTok, X, Facebook, Pinterest, LinkedIn and emerging platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help manage social calendars across multiple brands to ensure consistent, timely posting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Package and publish editorial content for social, tailoring tone, format, and presentation by platform and brand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write clear, compelling, on-brand captions and headlines&lt;/li&gt;
